The optical bandgap energy (Eg) of Ba1-xSrxTiO3 (x = 0–0.3) samples was determined by the Kubelkae-Munk method. The latter was used to extract Eg values, as well as stimulating the measured diffuse reflectance with high accuracy (Badapanda et al. 2015). The Kubelkae-Munk equation for each wavelength is represented by the following equation:7FR=(1-R)22R=kS\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
